00:02:00.559 --> 00:02:04.720
The question that was submitted specifically has to do

00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:08.839
with when will tongues cease or when did tongues cease?

00:02:08.839 --> 00:02:10.479
And so that's why we find ourselves here

00:02:10.479 --> 00:02:13.240
in 1 Corinthians 13 and verse number eight,

00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:16.080
really as a springboard into the message this evening.

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:18.479
We'll be looking again, as we did this morning,

00:02:18.479 --> 00:02:20.479
we'll be looking at a number of different portions

00:02:20.479 --> 00:02:22.759
of scripture within the Bible

00:02:22.759 --> 00:02:24.199
in order to answer the question.

00:02:24.199 --> 00:02:27.559
But here in 1 Corinthians 13 and verse number eight,

00:02:27.559 --> 00:02:30.679
the Bible says, charity never faileth.

00:02:30.679 --> 00:02:34.220
But whether there be prophecies, they shall fail.

00:02:34.220 --> 00:02:36.800
Now understand that it's not speaking about prophecies

00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:38.800
not coming to pass,

00:02:38.800 --> 00:02:42.899
meaning that they're going to cease to be given

00:02:42.899 --> 00:02:44.360
in the manner in which it's speaking here

00:02:44.360 --> 00:02:45.559
of these sign gifts.

00:02:45.559 --> 00:02:46.800
And then it continues and says,

00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:49.740
whether there be tongues, they shall cease.

00:02:49.740 --> 00:02:52.839
Whether there be knowledge, it shall vanish away.

00:02:52.839 --> 00:02:56.479
For we know in part and we prophesy in part,

00:02:56.479 --> 00:02:59.759
but when that which is perfect is come,

00:02:59.759 --> 00:03:02.800
then that which is in part shall be done away.

00:03:02.800 --> 00:03:04.960
When I was a child, I spake as a child,

00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:07.639
I understood as a child, I thought as a child,

00:03:07.639 --> 00:03:11.759
but when I became a man, I put away childish things.

00:03:11.759 --> 00:03:14.759
For now we see through a glass darkly,

00:03:14.759 --> 00:03:18.000
but then face to face, now I know in part,

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:21.960
but then shall I know even as also I am known.

00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:26.320
And now abideth faith, hope, charity, these three,

00:03:26.320 --> 00:03:29.160
but the greatest of these is charity.

00:03:29.160 --> 00:03:31.000
And so we see right in the midst of verse number eight,

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.360
the Bible says specifically,

00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:35.639
whether there be tongues, they shall cease.

00:03:35.639 --> 00:03:37.160
In order to answer the question

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:39.479
with regard to tongue ceasing,

00:03:39.479 --> 00:03:42.720
I believe it's important for us to understand two things.

00:03:42.720 --> 00:03:45.160
Number one, I believe that we need to understand

00:03:45.160 --> 00:03:47.399
the purpose of tongues,

00:03:47.399 --> 00:03:48.880
and then we also need to understand

00:03:48.880 --> 00:03:51.559
the biblical usage of tongues.

00:03:51.559 --> 00:03:54.800
If we can understand the purpose of tongues

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:56.899
and the biblical usage of tongues,

00:03:56.899 --> 00:03:59.119
then it helps us to be able to answer the question

00:03:59.119 --> 00:04:02.720
with regard to what it says here in 1 Corinthians 13, eight,

00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:05.720
whether there be tongues, they shall cease.

00:04:05.720 --> 00:04:09.259
So we begin to dig in and we understand this evening

00:04:09.259 --> 00:04:11.039
that within 1 Corinthians 13,

00:04:11.039 --> 00:04:12.720
really beginning in chapter 12

00:04:12.720 --> 00:04:14.539
and all the way through chapter 14,

00:04:14.539 --> 00:04:18.179
the apostle Paul is addressing the church in Corinth

00:04:18.179 --> 00:04:20.279
about spiritual gifts.

00:04:20.279 --> 00:04:22.679
As he's addressing the church in Corinth

00:04:22.679 --> 00:04:23.880
regarding spiritual gifts,

00:04:23.880 --> 00:04:25.339
it's important for us to understand

00:04:25.339 --> 00:04:27.059
some fundamental truths.

00:04:27.059 --> 00:04:30.000
Number one, I would say that as we have

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:34.839
an understanding of the audience to whom Paul is writing,

00:04:34.839 --> 00:04:36.320
this is a carnal church,

00:04:36.320 --> 00:04:38.959
this is a church that's dealing with

00:04:38.959 --> 00:04:41.239
all sorts of carnality and competition

00:04:41.239 --> 00:04:43.359
and saying, I have this spiritual gift

00:04:43.359 --> 00:04:44.799
and so I'm better than you are,

00:04:44.799 --> 00:04:47.940
and there's all of this comparison and competitiveness

00:04:47.940 --> 00:04:49.880
and all of this carnality.

00:04:50.480 --> 00:04:53.920
And he says that he can't speak to them as unto spiritual.

00:04:53.920 --> 00:04:54.739
Why?

00:04:54.739 --> 00:04:55.579
Because they're carnal.

00:04:55.579 --> 00:04:59.959
And so we understand the audience that Paul is writing to

00:04:59.959 --> 00:05:03.160
and we find that as Paul is giving them the truth

00:05:03.160 --> 00:05:05.500
with regard to spiritual gifts,

00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:09.739
there was obviously some matter, excuse me, of confusion

00:05:09.739 --> 00:05:12.720
because he starts in 1 Corinthians 12 in verse one

00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:15.959
and says, now concerning spiritual gifts, brethren,

00:05:15.959 --> 00:05:19.399
I would not have you ignorant.

00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:20.760
And so what is Paul saying?

00:05:20.760 --> 00:05:22.440
He wants them to be informed.

00:05:22.440 --> 00:05:25.880
He wants them to understand these spiritual gifts.

00:05:25.880 --> 00:05:28.059
He wants them to have an understanding

00:05:28.059 --> 00:05:31.640
of how God is working and what God is doing

00:05:31.640 --> 00:05:34.160
and the purpose of these spiritual gifts.

00:05:34.160 --> 00:05:36.920
He tells them in the first chapter,

00:05:36.920 --> 00:05:38.600
in chapter one in verse number seven,

00:05:38.600 --> 00:05:41.480
so that you come behind in no gift.

00:05:41.480 --> 00:05:44.239
And so we find that the gifts, they were gifted,

00:05:44.239 --> 00:05:46.640
they had spiritual gifts, they'd receive them.

00:05:46.640 --> 00:05:49.440
Just as we'd understand from 1 Peter

00:05:49.440 --> 00:05:54.200
that the Bible says, as every man hath received the gift,

00:05:54.200 --> 00:05:56.679
even so let him minister.

00:05:56.679 --> 00:05:59.799
And so we find that if you're saved this evening,

00:05:59.799 --> 00:06:02.820
you've been given a spiritual gift.

00:06:02.820 --> 00:06:05.559
Now, Paul is going to give them instruction

00:06:05.559 --> 00:06:08.779
because there's an element of ignorance

00:06:08.779 --> 00:06:11.440
that they have with regard to spiritual gifts.

00:06:11.440 --> 00:06:14.200
So fundamentally, it's important

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:16.440
that we have an understanding of spiritual gifts

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:21.320
generally, and then as we speak about tongues specifically,

00:06:21.320 --> 00:06:24.700
it will enable us to answer the question

00:06:24.700 --> 00:06:28.359
with regard to when tongues will cease.

00:06:28.359 --> 00:06:31.299
I do not think that it's a matter of arguing

00:06:31.299 --> 00:06:34.799
whether they will cease, for the Bible plainly says

00:06:34.799 --> 00:06:39.040
that whether there be tongues, they shall cease.

00:06:39.040 --> 00:06:42.700
So the question that arises is when will this take place?

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:44.920
Has this already taken place?

00:06:44.920 --> 00:06:47.279
And we try to again, answer that question

00:06:47.279 --> 00:06:51.320
by understanding the purpose and the biblical use of tongues.

00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:55.440
Now, let me say this, the Bible gives us three books

00:06:55.440 --> 00:06:59.720
that deal with, that Paul touches on spiritual gifts.

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:02.600
